question: Which Japanese spacecraft has recently started its journey home from asteroid Ryugu?
explanation: Japan\'s Hayabusa2 spacecraft has departed from a distant asteroid, starting its yearlong journey home after successfully completing its mission to bring back soil samples and data that could provide clues to the origins of the solar system. Hayabusa2 made two touchdowns on the asteroid and successfully collected data and samples during its one-and-a-half-year mission since arriving there in June 2018.
